def semicircleReal (μ : ℝ) (v : ℝ≥0) : Measure ℝ :=
  if v = 0 then Measure.dirac μ else volume.withDensity (semicirclePDF μ v)
```

This defines the semicircle distribution as a measure on the real numbers. When `v = 0`, it's a Dirac measure at `μ`. When `v ≠ 0`, it's the volume measure weighted by the semicircle PDF.

